<subSubSection lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="188" pageId="8" pageNumber="187" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="8.[136,1452,1840,2080]" pageId="8" pageNumber="187">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,318,1840,1866]" pageId="8" pageNumber="187">Etymology</emphasis>
:—The name chosen for this new species honors its collector, João Eduardo dos Santos, responsible for the preservation of an important fragment of Atlantic Forest in the county of Itapebi, 
<collectingRegion box="[1137,1264,1876,1902]" country="Brazil" name="Bahia" pageId="8" pageNumber="187">Bahia state</collectingRegion>
, and responsible for several botanical descoveries.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[136,1452,1840,2080]" lastBlockId="9.[136,1452,158,398]" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="188" pageId="8" pageNumber="187">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,348,1946,1972]" pageId="8" pageNumber="187">Observations</emphasis>
:— 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Leme &amp; E. H. Souza" authorityYear="2021" box="[384,616,1947,1973]" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Cryptanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="8" pageNumber="187" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="santosii">
<emphasis box="[384,616,1947,1973]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="187">Cryptanthus santosii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is morphologically closely related to 
<taxonomicName authority="Leme &amp; L. Kollmann" authorityName="Leme &amp; L. Kollmann" box="[1035,1451,1947,1973]" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Cryptanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="8" pageNumber="187" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="walkerianus">
<emphasis box="[1035,1204,1947,1973]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="187">C. walkerianus</emphasis>
Leme &amp; L. Kollmann
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Leme, E. M. C. &amp; Till, W. &amp; Kollmann, L. J. C. &amp; Moura, R. K. de &amp; Ribeiro, O. B." box="[144,389,1982,2009]" pageId="8" pageNumber="187" pagination="61 - 100" refId="ref7877" refString="Leme, E. M. C., Till, W., Kollmann, L. J. C., Moura, R. K. de &amp; Ribeiro, O. B. C (2014) Miscellaneous new species of Brazilian Bromeliaceae - III. Phytotaxa 177 (2): 61 - 100. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / phytotaxa. 177.2.1" type="journal article" year="2014">
Leme 
<emphasis box="[218,269,1982,2008]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="187">et al</emphasis>
. 2014: 83
</bibRefCitation>
), a typical inhabitant of the low elevated Atlantic Forest of the state of 
<collectingRegion box="[1212,1281,1982,2008]" country="Brazil" name="Bahia" pageId="8" pageNumber="187">Bahia</collectingRegion>
. However, this new species differs from it by its longer leaves, with longer petioles and narrower blades. On the other hand, the inflorescence has an inconspicuous central head of staminate flowers, sepals are longer with broader lobes which are densely and remotely denticulate, not entire. Finally, petals are longer and acute, not obtuse, forming a longer basal tube.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[136,1452,158,398]" pageId="9" pageNumber="188">
The long petiolate leaves of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Leme &amp; E. H. Souza" authorityYear="2021" box="[513,634,230,256]" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Cryptanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="9" pageNumber="188" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="santosii">
<emphasis box="[513,634,230,256]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="188">C. santosii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
make it also morphologically close to 
<taxonomicName authority="Leme (2002 b: 15)" authorityName="Leme" authorityPageNumber="15" authorityYear="2002" box="[1077,1446,229,256]" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Cryptanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="9" pageNumber="188" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="teretifolius">
<emphasis box="[1077,1231,229,256]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="188">C. teretifolius</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Leme, E. M. C." box="[1240,1446,229,256]" pageId="9" pageNumber="188" pagination="15 - 16" refId="ref7693" refString="Leme, E. M. C. (2002 b) Cryptanthus teretifolius, a new species from the coastal zone of Espirito Santo. Cryptanthus Society Journal 17: 15 - 16." type="journal article" year="2002">Leme (2002b: 15)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, which grows in the coastal sector of 
<collectingRegion box="[556,779,265,291]" country="Brazil" name="Espirito Santo" pageId="9" pageNumber="188">Espírito Santo state</collectingRegion>
, near the city of Vitória. The most important differences to this species are the leaf blades with longer petioles (
<quantity box="[731,845,300,327]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.45" metricValueMax="5.7" metricValueMin="3.2" pageId="9" pageNumber="188" unit="cm" value="44.5" valueMax="57.0" valueMin="32.0">32–57 cm</quantity>
<emphasis box="[854,877,301,326]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="188">vs</emphasis>
. 
<quantity box="[892,995,300,327]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" metricValueMax="2.2" metricValueMin="0.8" pageId="9" pageNumber="188" unit="cm" value="15.0" valueMax="22.0" valueMin="8.0">8–22 cm</quantity>
), which are strongly “U”-channeled (
<emphasis box="[1421,1444,301,326]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="188">vs</emphasis>
. involute-subulate and terete in cross section), one of its striking differences, as well as the longer sepals (
<quantity box="[1294,1415,336,362]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.95" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="1.9" pageId="9" pageNumber="188" unit="mm" value="19.5" valueMax="20.0" valueMin="19.0">19–20 mm</quantity>
<emphasis box="[1421,1444,336,361]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="188">vs</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[136,162,372,397]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="188">ca</emphasis>
. 
<quantity box="[176,259,371,398]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" pageId="9" pageNumber="188" unit="mm" value="16.0">16 mm</quantity>
), and petals with acute apex (
<emphasis box="[590,613,372,397]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="188">vs</emphasis>
. rounded to slightly cucullate).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
